definitions.definition: Of a side that is facing away from the axis or central line, such as the underside of a leaf, or the back of an animal.
Not in the axis. Applied to an embryo placed out of the axis of the seed.

main_definition: ( botany , zoology ) Of a side that is facing away from the axis or central line, such as the underside of a leaf, or the back of an animal. [Mid 19 century.]
secondary_definitions: ( botany ) Not in the axis. Applied to an embryo placed out of the axis of the seed.
